But…

268
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:00,000
Aren't you in a rush?

269
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:03,760
You have to discipline Kongkwan.

270
00:22:03,840 --> 00:22:05,320
She can't use force like that.

271
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:07,320
Does no one at home teach her?

272
00:22:09,320 --> 00:22:12,880
Before you complain, why don't we
hear the whole story first?

273
00:22:15,840 --> 00:22:17,320
Please continue, Teacher.

274
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:22,040
I asked the students
to form a group for an activity.

275
00:22:22,120 --> 00:22:23,880
Then, Kongkwan had a fight
with her classmates.

276
00:22:24,560 --> 00:22:27,040
She said Satang and Gino made fun of her.

277
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:32,200
Made fun of her? About what?

278
00:22:33,760 --> 00:22:34,960
They said…

279
00:22:36,560 --> 00:22:39,240
that you're a bad person
who dates many men.

280
00:22:39,320 --> 00:22:40,560
Something like that.

281
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:45,320
Did you tell your kids that nonsense?

282
00:22:45,960 --> 00:22:48,360
I'm sure kids
can't think that on their own.

283
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:51,240
I didn't say anything much.

284
00:22:51,320 --> 00:22:53,360
I just told them what I saw.

285
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:56,280
That's all. They probably remembered it.

286
00:22:56,880 --> 00:23:00,160
You're saying those things
when you don't even know the truth.

287
00:23:00,840 --> 00:23:02,880
You two have no right to judge me.

288
00:23:05,280 --> 00:23:06,120
Alright,

289
00:23:06,960 --> 00:23:09,360
it's bad enough
that the kids are fighting.

290
00:23:09,960 --> 00:23:11,480
We don't need to fight too.

291
00:23:12,520 --> 00:23:14,440
I asked you all to come here today

292
00:23:14,520 --> 00:23:18,480
because I don't want your issues
to cause trauma for the kids.

293
00:23:19,120 --> 00:23:22,600
After all, they're at an age
where they're old enough

294
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:23,800
to understand things.

295
00:23:27,840 --> 00:23:29,840
I must apologize, Teacher,

296
00:23:30,640 --> 00:23:33,160
but none of it is true.

297
00:23:33,760 --> 00:23:35,880
I'll explain it to my daughter.

298
00:23:35,960 --> 00:23:39,480
I must ask you to be more careful.

299
00:23:39,560 --> 00:23:41,520
Whatever kids shouldn't hear,

300
00:23:41,600 --> 00:23:44,000
please don't say it when they're near.

301
00:23:44,600 --> 00:23:48,040
Children may not be able
to differentiate things.

302
00:23:50,280 --> 00:23:53,000
I'll let it slide this time

303
00:23:53,960 --> 00:23:56,720
because what happened
was caused by adults,

304
00:23:57,760 --> 00:24:00,320
so we shouldn't blame it on the kids.

305
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:06,000
I just hope adults like us
can set a good example for the kids,

306
00:24:06,080 --> 00:24:08,400
and I hope this kind of thing
won't happen again.

307
00:24:08,480 --> 00:24:10,000
- Okay.
- Okay.

308
00:24:10,080 --> 00:24:11,080
Okay.

309
00:24:14,840 --> 00:24:15,800
{\an8}‪FOR SCHOOL DIRECTORS AND ADMINISTRATORS

310
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:17,600
{\an8}Don't cry, Kongkwan.

311
00:24:17,680 --> 00:24:19,880
I'll be right by your side.

312
00:24:19,960 --> 00:24:22,480
I won't cry because I know
my mom's not like that.

313
00:24:23,560 --> 00:24:25,040
Of course she is!

314
00:24:25,120 --> 00:24:26,200
That's what my mom said.

315
00:24:32,840 --> 00:24:34,400
Kongkwan, honey.

316
00:24:42,360 --> 00:24:43,480
Kongkwan,

317
00:24:44,560 --> 00:24:46,120
did you push your friend?

318
00:24:46,880 --> 00:24:51,040
Yes. But Satang insulted you first.

319
00:24:51,120 --> 00:24:52,720
And do you believe what she said?

320
00:24:54,320 --> 00:24:55,520
Exactly.

321
00:24:56,040 --> 00:24:58,440
What she said isn't true.

322
00:24:59,240 --> 00:25:00,960
But you pushed her,

323
00:25:01,040 --> 00:25:04,000
and you hurt her, so what should you do?

324
00:25:04,080 --> 00:25:05,680
Apologize.

325
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:07,920
Go.

326
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:11,160
I'm sorry.

327
00:25:12,520 --> 00:25:14,240
Gino and Satang,

328
00:25:14,320 --> 00:25:17,040
you have to say sorry
for making fun of her, too.

329
00:25:21,680 --> 00:25:23,560
- I'm sorry.
- I'm sorry.

330
00:25:28,360 --> 00:25:30,960
If there's nothing else,
we'll be going now.

331
00:25:31,720 --> 00:25:32,720
Let's go, honey.

332
00:25:34,360 --> 00:25:35,600
Let's go.

333
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:43,720
Come on, Poonpun. Let's go.

334
00:25:44,800 --> 00:25:47,600
Come on. Say goodbye to your teacher.

335
00:25:51,760 --> 00:25:53,320
Thank you, Teacher.

336
00:25:53,400 --> 00:25:55,120
I'll make sure it doesn't happen again.

337
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:56,440
Okay.

338
00:25:57,280 --> 00:25:58,480
Let's go.

339
00:26:16,760 --> 00:26:17,880
Daddy.

340
00:26:17,960 --> 00:26:18,920
How'd it go, Mook?

341
00:26:19,720 --> 00:26:21,760
We worked it out. Everything's fine.

342
00:26:24,440 --> 00:26:25,320
How are you?

343
00:26:32,040 --> 00:26:33,120
- Are you hungry?
- Yes?

344
00:26:33,200 --> 00:26:34,760
I'll be going now.

345
00:26:34,840 --> 00:26:37,440
Let's talk about work later.

346
00:26:38,480 --> 00:26:39,320
But…

347
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:49,800
Are you mad at me?

348
00:26:52,760 --> 00:26:55,080
No. Not at all,

349
00:26:55,160 --> 00:26:57,040
but if anyone says anything again,

350
00:26:57,120 --> 00:26:59,600
come tell me first, okay?

351
00:27:02,880 --> 00:27:03,920
What happened, Mook?

352
00:27:06,800 --> 00:27:08,320
I'll tell you later.

353
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:11,560
Guys, do we want pizza today?

354
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:14,200
Yes! I want pizza!

355
00:27:14,280 --> 00:27:15,680
What about you, Kongkwan?

356
00:27:16,440 --> 00:27:18,680
- Okay, then let's go.
- Let's go.

357
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:21,160
- What should we get?
- I don't know.

358
00:27:21,680 --> 00:27:22,520
Are you hungry, Kongkwan?

359
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:24,320
- Cheese pizza?
- Sure.

360
00:27:24,960 --> 00:27:26,040
Same as always.

361
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:28,440
- Why not try a different topping?
- Let's go.

362
00:27:29,120 --> 00:27:31,680
- No, thanks, I like the usual.
- No?

363
00:27:42,320 --> 00:27:44,040
What were you doing at the school?

364
00:27:45,120 --> 00:27:46,280
I went there with Mook.

365
00:27:48,360 --> 00:27:52,160
And why exactly did you go there with her?

366
00:27:53,400 --> 00:27:55,400
When you disappeared this morning,

367
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:58,400
things got so chaotic over there.

368
00:28:00,960 --> 00:28:03,000
I called and asked Mook to pick me up.

369
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:05,840
And…

370
00:28:05,920 --> 00:28:07,320
What is it, sir?

371
00:28:07,920 --> 00:28:10,200
Forget it. It's a long story.

372
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:15,560
Mr. Pitak,

373
00:28:16,360 --> 00:28:19,720
please arrange for both companies
to hear my decision.

374
00:28:20,520 --> 00:28:21,520
I've made up my mind.

375
00:28:22,520 --> 00:28:23,840
Sure, Mr. Thee.

376
00:28:38,840 --> 00:28:39,760
Here.

377
00:28:47,480 --> 00:28:48,680
Mook,

378
00:28:49,720 --> 00:28:52,920
I heard there was a commotion
at our office?

379
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:55,240
Are you alright?

380
00:28:56,360 --> 00:28:58,440
About Kuk's mother causing a scene, right?

381
00:29:00,040 --> 00:29:01,360
I'm used to it now.

382
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:05,920
Your haters will hate you,
no matter how good you behave.

383
00:29:07,560 --> 00:29:10,760
I think it depends on the person,

384
00:29:12,080 --> 00:29:15,840
but if they only act on emotion
and not reason,

385
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:17,440
it's probably hard to fix.

386
00:29:24,200 --> 00:29:26,040
Mook,

387
00:29:26,880 --> 00:29:29,240
why'd Mr. Thee want to come
to our office today?

388
00:29:29,840 --> 00:29:33,600
He called, asking me to pick him up
from Family Tour's trip.

389
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:37,360
He was probably unhappy,
so he wanted me to take him away.

390
00:29:38,320 --> 00:29:39,680
Why did it have to be you?

391
00:29:40,640 --> 00:29:44,760
I bet he's still angry
that I had a fight with him the other day,

392
00:29:45,560 --> 00:29:47,680
yet still he asked you to pick him up?

393
00:29:50,800 --> 00:29:53,840
Don't you think
he's acting a little strange?

394
00:29:55,560 --> 00:29:59,560
Maybe it's because I called
to make an appointment with him earlier.

395
00:30:00,240 --> 00:30:02,840
I wanted to clear the air
about that fight the other day.

396
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:05,240
It's probably just good timing.

397
00:30:10,480 --> 00:30:11,680
Is it good, honey?

398
00:30:13,200 --> 00:30:14,120
Is it good, Poonpun?

399
00:30:14,200 --> 00:30:15,480
It's so good.

400
00:30:15,560 --> 00:30:16,880
Want some french fries?

401
00:30:16,960 --> 00:30:17,920
Sure. Here.

402
00:30:21,160 --> 00:30:23,160
Here you go.

403
00:30:23,240 --> 00:30:24,960
Go to sleep, my good girl.

404
00:30:25,560 --> 00:30:27,800
You have to get up early to go to school.

405
00:30:29,960 --> 00:30:31,240
Mommy.

406
00:30:32,320 --> 00:30:33,320
What's up?

407
00:30:33,400 --> 00:30:38,040
You won't have many boyfriends
like they said, right?

408
00:30:41,120 --> 00:30:44,400
Is Daddy your boyfriend too?

409
00:30:52,440 --> 00:30:53,680
Kongkwan,

410
00:30:54,280 --> 00:30:57,400
even if Mommy and Daddy
aren't together anymore,

411
00:30:58,520 --> 00:31:01,680
we'll still be your mommy and daddy.

412
00:31:07,040 --> 00:31:08,680
Go to sleep, okay?

413
00:31:10,320 --> 00:31:14,120
Mommy will sleep holding you tonight.

414
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:15,680
Can I?

415
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:19,840
Come on.

416
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:27,320
<i>Why'd Mr. Thee want to come</i>
<i>to our office today?</i>

417
00:31:27,400 --> 00:31:31,720
<i>I bet he's still angry</i>
<i>that I had a fight with him the other day.</i>

418
00:31:31,800 --> 00:31:34,680
<i>Don't you think</i>
<i>he's acting a little strange?</i>

419
00:31:50,720 --> 00:31:52,560
You did your best.

420
00:31:52,640 --> 00:31:55,000
It's okay if we don't win. Don't worry.

421
00:31:59,120 --> 00:32:00,720
Oh my.

422
00:32:01,240 --> 00:32:04,240
Yesterday you were all sweet
with that guy, and now it's this guy.

423
00:32:05,480 --> 00:32:07,400
How many more do you have
left in stock, Mook?

424
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:11,440
Have a little respect, would you?

425
00:32:12,040 --> 00:32:14,160
Act like you deserve it, then.

426
00:32:14,240 --> 00:32:16,240
Don't go smooching in a place like this.

427
00:32:18,360 --> 00:32:22,240
Should I sneak around and sleep with him
in a five-star hotel like you two did?

428
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:26,600
Is that what you call
dignified and honorable?

429
00:32:45,680 --> 00:32:49,320
Mr. Thee, I can explain about yesterday.

430
00:32:49,920 --> 00:32:51,200
That's alright.

431
00:32:51,280 --> 00:32:55,840
To me, taking care of your clients
is more important than your tour programs.

432
00:32:55,920 --> 00:32:58,600
If that's the case,
you don't have to worry.

433
00:32:58,680 --> 00:33:01,520
We're confident our service is number one.

434
00:33:02,520 --> 00:33:04,680
Shouldn't we let him decide that?

435
00:33:06,800 --> 00:33:09,520
Mr. Thee has invited
both your companies here today

436
00:33:09,600 --> 00:33:12,800
to announce the winner
of the You Are The One project.

437
00:33:13,440 --> 00:33:16,960
The winner will get to sign
a contract with us.

438
00:33:17,040 --> 00:33:20,080
First of all, I'd like to thank
both your companies

439
00:33:20,160 --> 00:33:21,600
for doing your best in the contest.

440
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:23,600
Let me preface by saying

441
00:33:24,360 --> 00:33:27,720
that I've never judged anyone
based on their background

442
00:33:27,800 --> 00:33:28,840
because it's in the past.

443
00:33:35,200 --> 00:33:37,240
What do you mean by that?

444
00:33:39,160 --> 00:33:42,800
I mean that I will make my decision
based on what I got

445
00:33:43,600 --> 00:33:45,360
and what I experienced firsthand only.

446
00:33:48,400 --> 00:33:52,520
And the company
that will sign a contract with us is…

447
00:33:54,080 --> 00:33:55,360
A Round Trip Travel.

448
00:33:57,560 --> 00:33:58,800
- Mook.
- Boss!

449
00:34:01,560 --> 00:34:03,000
What did Family Tour do wrong?

450
00:34:05,240 --> 00:34:06,560
You failed completely.

451
00:34:07,480 --> 00:34:10,520
Understanding the customer
is crucial in this line of work.

452
00:34:10,600 --> 00:34:13,080
I want to work with a travel agency

453
00:34:13,159 --> 00:34:16,520
that prioritizes
their clients' preferences, needs,

454
00:34:16,600 --> 00:34:18,840
and identity

455
00:34:19,719 --> 00:34:23,239
rather than organize
a big, fancy tour in hopes of winning.

456
00:34:24,760 --> 00:34:26,320
<i>You should've known</i>

457
00:34:26,920 --> 00:34:29,679
that Mr. Thee doesn't like a big fuss.

458
00:34:29,760 --> 00:34:31,840
Especially reporters.

459
00:34:31,920 --> 00:34:33,840
And in that program you sent us,

460
00:34:33,920 --> 00:34:36,320
you never mentioned
the press would be here.

461
00:34:38,440 --> 00:34:41,600
You'll regret underestimating us.

462
00:34:52,639 --> 00:34:54,639
He had a lot of hope for this project.

463
00:34:54,719 --> 00:34:56,560
I apologize on his behalf, Mr. Thee.

464
00:35:03,200 --> 00:35:07,160
Congrats, but we'll definitely see
each other again, Mook.

465
00:35:20,040 --> 00:35:22,400
Thank you for giving
A Round Trip Travel a chance.

466
00:35:23,200 --> 00:35:25,760
I must apologize about that day.

467
00:35:25,840 --> 00:35:28,120
That's alright. It was a misunderstanding.

468
00:35:29,440 --> 00:35:31,600
You should thank your employee instead.

469
00:35:33,120 --> 00:35:35,280
Your company only won today

470
00:35:36,640 --> 00:35:38,440
because she has the qualifications I need.

471
00:36:02,240 --> 00:36:03,280
Mr. Thee!

472
00:36:08,200 --> 00:36:09,800
May I have a moment?

473
00:36:17,360 --> 00:36:19,600
I wanted to thank you for yesterday.

474
00:36:20,360 --> 00:36:21,800
Is everything alright?

475
00:36:23,200 --> 00:36:24,280
Yes.

476
00:36:24,960 --> 00:36:26,160
You must be tired,

477
00:36:27,120 --> 00:36:31,040
being a single mom
and still having to work.

478
00:36:33,800 --> 00:36:35,400
You know about me?

479
00:36:36,000 --> 00:36:39,240
Yes, I know about you and Mr. Apichart.

480
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:44,560
I need to know the background
of all my partners.

481
00:36:44,640 --> 00:36:46,120
It's only natural.

482
00:36:50,160 --> 00:36:52,640
There's nothing wrong
with being a single mom.

483
00:36:53,840 --> 00:36:55,680
And no matter what state I'm in,

484
00:36:56,720 --> 00:37:00,760
I'd do anything for my daughter
so she'd grow up to be the happiest.

485
00:37:04,640 --> 00:37:05,560
Of course.

486
00:37:08,040 --> 00:37:09,880
At least you're a good mom.

487
00:37:11,520 --> 00:37:14,160
Your daughter must be really proud of you,

488
00:37:16,120 --> 00:37:19,520
unlike some mothers
who only care about themselves

489
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:23,640
and never wonder how their child is doing.

490
00:37:34,960 --> 00:37:37,120
Mook. There you are.

491
00:37:41,600 --> 00:37:43,160
I told everyone the result.

492
00:37:43,240 --> 00:37:45,280
We're celebrating after work tonight.

493
00:37:49,320 --> 00:37:50,560
If you don’t mind,

494
00:37:50,640 --> 00:37:53,080
I’d like to invite you to join us.

495
00:37:59,800 --> 00:38:02,840
Mr. Thee doesn't really like big crowds.

496
00:38:04,040 --> 00:38:05,160
I see.

497
00:38:05,240 --> 00:38:08,600
It seems I'll have to learn
about customer analysis from Mook.

498
00:38:22,160 --> 00:38:23,640
Thank you, Mook.

499
00:38:23,720 --> 00:38:25,640
We finally did it.

500
00:38:26,240 --> 00:38:29,200
I told you we'd win, no matter what.

501
00:38:32,720 --> 00:38:34,080
Did you book the tables yet?

502
00:38:34,160 --> 00:38:35,200
I did.

503
00:38:35,880 --> 00:38:40,320
{\an8}MRS. OH

504
00:38:49,640 --> 00:38:50,800
Hello, Mrs. Oh.

505
00:38:50,880 --> 00:38:52,200
Did you enjoy your vacation?

506
00:38:52,280 --> 00:38:54,640
<i>I enjoyed it so much</i>
<i>that it's hard to express.</i>

507
00:38:55,320 --> 00:38:56,760
<i>I have something to show you.</i>

508
00:38:57,440 --> 00:38:58,800
<i>I'll send it to you.</i>

509
00:39:23,240 --> 00:39:25,760
<i>My mom won't mind</i>
<i>If you wanna make a move</i>

510
00:39:25,840 --> 00:39:29,160
- Whoo! My mom won't mind.
- <i>La la la</i>

511
00:39:29,240 --> 00:39:31,760
<i>Ba ba ba</i>

512
00:39:31,840 --> 00:39:34,480
Heck yeah! Go, go!

513
00:39:34,560 --> 00:39:36,000
<i>She'll hand me over</i>

514
00:39:36,600 --> 00:39:38,720
My mom won't mind… Not you, though.

515
00:39:41,080 --> 00:39:42,880
<i>Future son-in-law</i>

516
00:39:45,920 --> 00:39:48,760
Let's drink to our victory!

517
00:39:48,840 --> 00:39:51,120
Here's to the toughness and resilience

518
00:39:51,200 --> 00:39:54,400
of our badass manager, Ms. Mook!

519
00:39:54,480 --> 00:39:55,760
- Yeah.
- Right.

520
00:39:55,840 --> 00:39:57,440
- Hear, hear.
- Hear, hear.

521
00:39:58,040 --> 00:40:01,200
- A Round Trip Travel, we slay!
- A Round Trip Travel, we slay!

522
00:40:01,280 --> 00:40:03,200
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

523
00:40:03,280 --> 00:40:04,200
Bottoms up!

524
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:05,200
What?

525
00:40:08,760 --> 00:40:10,680
What a shame. Mr. Thee should've come.

526
00:40:12,080 --> 00:40:13,640
Mr. Thee's not here.

527
00:40:13,720 --> 00:40:15,400
How about Mr. Tit for now?

528
00:40:15,480 --> 00:40:17,280
- Oh my.
- Wow.

529
00:40:17,360 --> 00:40:18,760
Look at him.

530
00:40:20,360 --> 00:40:21,440
You're nothing alike.

531
00:40:21,520 --> 00:40:23,760
You're like the sky and the abyss,
heaven and hell.

532
00:40:28,520 --> 00:40:29,920
Looks like fun.

533
00:40:31,080 --> 00:40:32,480
Can I join?

534
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:37,920
Prao.

535
00:40:46,920 --> 00:40:48,240
<i>Hello, Ms. Prao.</i>

536
00:40:48,320 --> 00:40:49,960
I can't get ahold of Pat.

537
00:40:50,040 --> 00:40:51,320
Is he at the office?

538
00:40:52,520 --> 00:40:54,440
He went to a meeting with a client.

539
00:40:54,520 --> 00:40:55,640
He isn't back yet.

540
00:40:55,720 --> 00:40:57,480
Please check his schedule for me.

541
00:40:57,560 --> 00:40:59,600
I'm inviting him
to an association event tonight.

542
00:41:00,760 --> 00:41:01,960
Tonight, he's having

543
00:41:02,040 --> 00:41:04,760
a celebration party with us
because we won the pitch.

544
00:41:04,840 --> 00:41:07,280
I just booked the restaurant.

545
00:41:08,120 --> 00:41:11,520
That's okay. Just send me the location.

546
00:41:11,600 --> 00:41:13,520
I'll send a gift to congratulate him.

547
00:41:14,360 --> 00:41:15,320
Of course.

548
00:41:26,920 --> 00:41:28,760
Why didn't you tell me you're coming?

549
00:41:28,840 --> 00:41:30,880
Well, then it wouldn't be a surprise.

550
00:41:34,880 --> 00:41:37,160
I wanted to congratulate you all today.

551
00:41:37,760 --> 00:41:40,800
Have a blast, everyone. It's all on me.

552
00:41:43,880 --> 00:41:44,880
Hey.

553
00:41:49,960 --> 00:41:51,040
Good evening, Mook.

554
00:41:51,560 --> 00:41:53,200
Good evening, Ms. Prao.

555
00:42:13,640 --> 00:42:15,760
<i>If only I could have you back</i>

556
00:42:15,840 --> 00:42:17,320
<i>Just to buy a little more time</i>

557
00:42:17,400 --> 00:42:20,600
<i>Even one minute would mean so much to me</i>

558
00:42:20,680 --> 00:42:24,120
- Shut it!
<i>- I beg of you</i>

559
00:42:24,200 --> 00:42:26,560
<i>Alone</i>

560
00:42:33,760 --> 00:42:35,400
Drink up! Why are you so quiet?

561
00:42:36,720 --> 00:42:37,560
Sure.

562
00:42:40,400 --> 00:42:41,880
Another glass.

563
00:42:42,400 --> 00:42:43,960
A Round Trip Travel.

564
00:42:45,000 --> 00:42:46,160
Come on.

565
00:43:47,200 --> 00:43:49,880
Mr. Pitak, do you know where
A Round Trip Travel is celebrating?

566
00:44:13,000 --> 00:44:16,560
I'd like to officially congratulate
all of you again.

567
00:44:18,560 --> 00:44:19,920
Thank you.

568
00:44:22,680 --> 00:44:23,640
Yeah.

569
00:44:34,840 --> 00:44:37,640
I bet this was thanks
to Mook again, right?

570
00:44:38,440 --> 00:44:40,480
We work as a team,

571
00:44:40,560 --> 00:44:43,720
so I think it's thanks to everyone.

572
00:44:50,600 --> 00:44:53,800
But I brought a special gift just for you.

573
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:04,840
Excuse me.

574
00:45:08,840 --> 00:45:10,760
{\an8}REWARD FOR BEST HUSBAND-STEALER

575
00:45:16,960 --> 00:45:18,360
What are you doing, Prao?

576
00:45:19,280 --> 00:45:22,440
Congratulating this girl
who's so good at everything, of course.

577
00:45:23,600 --> 00:45:27,080
Especially at stealing husbands.

578
00:45:28,560 --> 00:45:31,080
Prao, stop imagining things.

579
00:45:32,200 --> 00:45:33,880
Mook and I aren't what you think we are!

580
00:45:38,920 --> 00:45:39,840
Then what's this?

581
00:45:42,080 --> 00:45:45,600
She's dating both of you at once,
so you had to fight over her.

582
00:45:47,440 --> 00:45:50,520
So this picture was enough
for you to assume it all?

583
00:45:51,920 --> 00:45:54,960
Did you ever think to ask me
what happened earlier?

584
00:45:55,040 --> 00:45:56,400
Why should I?

585
00:45:59,160 --> 00:46:01,160
She's using work as a cover.

586
00:46:02,960 --> 00:46:04,680
I'm not stupid. I know her game!

587
00:46:05,280 --> 00:46:06,160
Hey.

588
00:46:06,240 --> 00:46:08,480
If you're not stupid,
pull yourself together.

589
00:46:09,000 --> 00:46:11,360
Don't just believe
what you see or hear them say.

590
00:46:12,840 --> 00:46:14,840
- Stop it!
- Prao!

591
00:46:14,920 --> 00:46:18,320
You think I wouldn't touch you
because Pat's backing you up?

592
00:46:18,400 --> 00:46:20,400
- Prao, stop it!
- Let go!

593
00:46:21,360 --> 00:46:23,680
- Hey! Hey!
- Ms. Prao!

594
00:46:23,760 --> 00:46:26,120
- Prao!
- You keep blaming other people

595
00:46:26,200 --> 00:46:28,120
for destroying your family,

596
00:46:28,720 --> 00:46:30,960
but you never see your own faults.

597
00:46:31,040 --> 00:46:33,600
You never thought about changing
to save your family!

598
00:46:34,360 --> 00:46:35,640
Take a look at yourself!

599
00:46:35,720 --> 00:46:36,880
Have you done your best?

600
00:46:36,960 --> 00:46:38,640
Ask yourself before blaming everyone!

601
00:46:39,240 --> 00:46:40,720
Don't act all wise now.

602
00:46:40,800 --> 00:46:42,640
I know you want to steal my husband!

603
00:46:42,720 --> 00:46:44,040
- Calm down, Ms. Prao!
- Prao!

604
00:46:44,120 --> 00:46:45,200
I… I…

605
00:46:45,280 --> 00:46:48,280
I think you should take
Ms. Primprao home, Mr. Pat.

606
00:46:48,360 --> 00:46:50,400
Prao, let's talk at home.

607
00:46:51,040 --> 00:46:51,920
I'm not leaving.

608
00:46:52,520 --> 00:46:54,520
I have to settle this with her today,

609
00:46:54,600 --> 00:46:56,720
so she'd stop taking what's mine!

610
00:46:56,800 --> 00:46:59,320
Let go of me!

611
00:46:59,400 --> 00:47:00,600
Prao!

612
00:47:00,680 --> 00:47:03,760
If you didn't exist,
my husband wouldn't be this way!

613
00:47:03,840 --> 00:47:05,040
Remember that, Mook!

614
00:47:05,640 --> 00:47:06,640
Let go!

615
00:47:12,120 --> 00:47:15,200
Mook, are you okay?

616
00:47:31,240 --> 00:47:34,360
Mook. Mook, Mook.

617
00:47:34,440 --> 00:47:37,000
Mook. Mook!

618
00:47:37,080 --> 00:47:38,040
Where are you going?

619
00:47:38,120 --> 00:47:39,520
Should I come with you?

620
00:47:39,600 --> 00:47:42,400
It's okay. I want to be alone.

621
00:47:43,840 --> 00:47:46,880
Mr. Suetrong, please handle things here.

622
00:47:46,960 --> 00:47:48,160
Got it.

623
00:47:48,240 --> 00:47:50,000
Mook, I…

624
00:50:44,440 --> 00:50:45,760
Thank you.

625
00:50:53,720 --> 00:50:56,920
Why do you always see me
when I'm in this state?

626
00:50:58,640 --> 00:51:00,000
I'm rather happy

627
00:51:01,040 --> 00:51:04,160
to see you when you're in this state.

628
00:51:06,680 --> 00:51:10,960
At least, I feel like
I can be your support.

629
00:51:17,720 --> 00:51:19,560
Whatever's bugging you,

630
00:51:21,040 --> 00:51:23,040
can you tell me about it?

631
00:51:29,240 --> 00:51:32,680
Sometimes when you get to vent,

632
00:51:34,720 --> 00:51:36,920
it might help you feel better.

633
00:51:49,160 --> 00:51:51,480
It's just a little misunderstanding.

634
00:51:54,680 --> 00:51:58,680
Ms. Prao, my boss' wife,
she misunderstood me.

635
00:52:00,720 --> 00:52:04,880
We ran a background check on Mr. Anapat,
CEO of A Round Trip Travel.

636
00:52:04,960 --> 00:52:06,480
There's nothing of concern.

637
00:52:07,120 --> 00:52:08,960
He's got a clean track record.

638
00:52:09,040 --> 00:52:11,520
Working with him should be no problem.

639
00:52:12,280 --> 00:52:13,920
You said he's married?

640
00:52:14,000 --> 00:52:15,480
Yes, he's married.

641
00:52:16,080 --> 00:52:19,960
They have a son. His wife is Ms. Primprao.

642
00:52:20,040 --> 00:52:22,600
She's the daughter of Mr. Pansak,
the famous politician.

643
00:52:29,520 --> 00:52:31,800
Is it about what happened
at the school that day too?

644
00:52:36,440 --> 00:52:37,760
My daughter,

645
00:52:39,080 --> 00:52:41,320
she goes to the same school
as my boss' son.

646
00:52:43,880 --> 00:52:46,280
Because we're so close,

647
00:52:47,520 --> 00:52:49,720
Ms. Prao misunderstood us.

648
00:52:50,320 --> 00:52:54,080
And your relationship with Mr. Pat,

649
00:52:55,280 --> 00:52:56,280
what's it like?

650
00:52:58,560 --> 00:53:00,200
He's both my boss

651
00:53:01,400 --> 00:53:03,400
and someone I can talk to about anything.

652
00:53:07,920 --> 00:53:10,400
We're just good friends.

653
00:53:23,880 --> 00:53:27,080
It's really late. If you'll excuse me.

654
00:53:27,840 --> 00:53:31,280
As for the robe,
I'll return it after it's washed.

655
00:53:31,360 --> 00:53:32,320
Wait.

656
00:53:33,640 --> 00:53:36,200
I can't let you go home in this state.

657
00:53:44,080 --> 00:53:45,200
Follow me.

658
00:54:04,120 --> 00:54:07,280
Sorry, do you have other ones that's--

659
00:54:07,360 --> 00:54:09,120
I think this one looks great.

660
00:54:11,520 --> 00:54:12,440
We'll buy this one.

661
00:54:12,520 --> 00:54:14,360
I'll bag up your old clothes for you.

662
00:54:15,880 --> 00:54:17,800
Sorry, how much is it?

663
00:54:17,880 --> 00:54:19,280
Four thousand nine hundred.

664
00:54:21,240 --> 00:54:25,000
I'll buy a different one, then.

665
00:54:25,080 --> 00:54:26,240
Is there any that's cheaper?

666
00:54:26,320 --> 00:54:27,400
It's fine.

667
00:54:28,280 --> 00:54:29,880
Just buy me dinner someday.

668
00:54:33,520 --> 00:54:38,440
Are you sure you won't send me
a bill later like last time?

669
00:54:51,920 --> 00:54:52,880
Yes, Boss?

670
00:54:56,560 --> 00:54:57,920
I'm alright.

671
00:55:00,640 --> 00:55:03,440
I'm with Mr. Thee now.

672
00:55:17,600 --> 00:55:19,640
I thought we were clear, Prao.

673
00:55:19,720 --> 00:55:21,560
If you keep this up, I won't stand for it.

674
00:55:21,640 --> 00:55:24,800
You won't? I'm the one
who's standing for it!

675
00:55:25,440 --> 00:55:27,240
Even a three-year-old
can tell she likes you!

676
00:55:28,480 --> 00:55:30,400
Fire her and I'll stop.

677
00:55:30,480 --> 00:55:32,960
No! Mook's done nothing wrong.

678
00:55:33,040 --> 00:55:35,080
She’s always given her all for my company.

679
00:55:36,040 --> 00:55:37,720
You're always defending her.

680
00:55:37,800 --> 00:55:39,560
How far have you two really gone?

681
00:55:39,640 --> 00:55:41,800
Can you stop having those filthy thoughts?

682
00:55:42,680 --> 00:55:44,720
Mook and I have never slept together.

683
00:55:46,000 --> 00:55:47,480
And let me tell you this.

684
00:55:47,560 --> 00:55:49,800
Leave her alone.
Don't ever accuse her again,

685
00:55:51,040 --> 00:55:52,640
or you will regret it.

686
00:55:56,600 --> 00:55:57,800
Try me, then.

687
00:55:59,200 --> 00:56:01,040
I'll make sure she pays,

688
00:56:01,760 --> 00:56:03,800
and your stupid travel agency
will suffer too!

689
00:56:07,440 --> 00:56:10,320
Pat, stop! Pat!

690
00:56:10,400 --> 00:56:11,840
Don't you walk away!

691
00:56:12,440 --> 00:56:13,440
Pat!

692
00:56:31,440 --> 00:56:32,920
{\an8}- So what is it?
- What does it mean?

693
00:56:33,000 --> 00:56:35,200
{\an8}- How'd you two meet?
- Mr. Thee.

694
00:56:35,280 --> 00:56:38,640
{\an8}Ms. Veluree and I are seeing each other.

695
00:56:38,720 --> 00:56:42,080
{\an8}Her company only won
because she slept with him.

696
00:56:42,160 --> 00:56:44,360
{\an8}It's all over the news now.

697
00:56:44,440 --> 00:56:46,320
{\an8}Mr. Thee's dating her.

698
00:56:46,400 --> 00:56:47,880
{\an8}Can I see?

699
00:56:57,120 --> 00:56:58,480
{\an8}I want an answer…

700
00:57:01,920 --> 00:57:03,840
{\an8}that comes from your true feelings.

701
00:57:58,160 --> 00:58:00,440
Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

